      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While minimum wage hikes aim to improve workers' quality of life, they can also increase operational costs for small businesses like your coffee shop in rural areas. In low-rent, low-cost locations, a balance must be found between fair wages and maintaining competitive pricing for customers. If the costs rise significantly, your business may need to adjust by exploring efficiencies, increasing prices moderately, or cutting non-essential expenses. However, if the wage increase is too high, it might become marginally difficult to sustain your venture, especially if you're already paying competitive wages. It is crucial to thoroughly analyze your unique economic situation to make an informed decision.",
